snippet: The remains included some perpetrators of deadly suicide bombings carried out against Israelis in the last decade, while the oldest of the remains had been held by Israel since 1975.
abstract: Israel returns the remains of 91 Palestinians, most of them killed while carrying out attacks against Israelis in the last decade, to the West Bank and Gaza in a move described by Israeli officials as a gesture intended to help bring the Palestinians back to peace negotiations.

byline.contributor: Khaled Abu Aker contributed reporting from Ramallah, and Fares Akram from Gaza.

lead_paragraph: The remains included some perpetrators of deadly suicide bombings carried out against Israelis in the last decade, while the oldest of the remains had been held by Israel since 1975.

headline.main: Israel, in Gesture, Repatriates Bodies of 91 Palestinians
headline.print_headline: Trying to Restart Talks, Israel Returns Bodies of Palestinians to West Bank and Gaza
